---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalContent from '../../components/legal/LegalContent.astro';
import { useTranslations } from '../../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en' as const;
const t = useTranslations(locale);
---
<BaseLayout title={t('legal.agbTitle')} locale={locale}>
  <main>
    <LegalContent title="Terms and conditions">
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> April 2026</p>
      <p>
        <em>This translation is provided for convenience. The German version on
        /agb is the legally binding text.</em>
      </p>

      <h2>§ 1 Scope</h2>
      <p>
        These general terms and conditions (“Terms") apply to all contracts between
        Nestor Segura, Heidmühlenweg 54, 25336 Elmshorn (the “Contractor") and his clients
        (the “Client") covering services in web design, web development, search engine
        optimisation (SEO), content strategy and digital-marketing consulting.
      </p>
      <p>
        Deviating, conflicting or supplementary terms and conditions of the Client become part
        of the contract only if and to the extent that the Contractor has expressly agreed to
        their validity in writing.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 2 Subject matter and scope of services</h2>
      <p>
        The Contractor provides services in web design and web development (in particular using
        Astro, Sanity and Cloudflare Workers), search engine optimisation, content strategy and
        strategic consulting. The specific scope of services is set out in the individual offer
        or project contract.
      </p>
      <p>
        Changes to the agreed scope of services require a written agreement (text form is
        sufficient). Additionally commissioned services are billed separately.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Contractor is entitled to engage qualified subcontractors. He remains responsible
        for the proper performance of the service.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 3 Offer and conclusion of contract</h2>
      <p>
        Offers from the Contractor are non-binding unless expressly marked as binding. The
        contract is concluded by written order confirmation from the Contractor or by actual
        commencement of the service.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Client warrants that the information provided by him is complete and accurate.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 4 Client's duties to cooperate</h2>
      <p>
        The Client provides the Contractor in good time and in full with all the information,
        materials and access required to perform the service — in particular texts, images,
        logos, brand guidelines and access credentials to systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        Delays caused by incomplete or late cooperation by the Client are not borne by the
        Contractor. Additional effort resulting therefrom may be charged separately.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 5 Remuneration and payment terms</h2>
      <p>
        Remuneration is based on the respective individual offer. All prices are in euros plus
        the applicable statutory value-added tax.
      </p>
      <p>
        Unless otherwise agreed in the individual contract, the following payment schedule applies
        to project contracts: 50% of the total fee is due upon order placement and the remaining
        50% upon project completion.
      </p>
      <p>
        Invoices are due for payment without deduction within 14 days of the invoice date.
        Ongoing services (e.g. monthly SEO or maintenance) are invoiced monthly in advance.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 6 Acceptance</h2>
      <p>
        Where work products are owed that are subject to acceptance, the Client must review
        and accept them in writing within 14 days of delivery. Acceptance may not be refused for
        minor defects. Acceptance is deemed to have been granted if the Client does not raise
        any written defect notice within the period stated, or if the Client uses the work
        productively.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 7 Rights of use and intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        Upon full payment of the agreed fee, the Client receives a non-exclusive right, unlimited
        in time and territory, to use the works created under the contract for the purpose agreed
        in the contract.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Contractor is entitled to use work created for the Client as a reference (in particular
        in the portfolio and on social media), unless the Client expressly objects in writing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Source files, drafts and unreleased intermediate results remain with the Contractor.
        Third-party licences (e.g. stock photos, fonts, SaaS tools) are to be acquired separately
        by the Client or are charged on a cost basis.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 8 Warranty and liability</h2>
      <p>
        The Contractor performs his services with the diligence of a prudent businessman, but does
        not owe any specific commercial outcome (in particular no specific rankings, conversion
        rates or revenue figures).
      </p>
      <p>
        In the event of defects, the Client must give the Contractor an opportunity to remedy them.
        If two attempts at remediation fail, the Client may reduce the fee or withdraw from the
        contract.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Contractor's liability is limited to intent and gross negligence. In the case of slight
        negligence, the Contractor is only liable for breach of essential contractual obligations
        (cardinal obligations); in this case liability is limited in amount to the foreseeable
        damage typical of the contract at the time of conclusion of the contract, but at most
        to the net contract value.
      </p>
      <p>
        The above limitations of liability do not apply to damage arising from injury to life,
        body or health, or to claims under the German Product Liability Act.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 9 Confidentiality and data protection</h2>
      <p>
        Both parties undertake to treat all confidential information of the other party obtained
        in the course of the cooperation as confidential. This obligation continues beyond the
        end of the contractual relationship.
      </p>
      <p>
        Insofar as the Contractor processes personal data on behalf of the Client in the course
        of performing the contract, the parties shall conclude a separate data processing
        agreement in accordance with Art. 28 GDPR.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 10 Term and termination</h2>
      <p>
        Project contracts end upon acceptance of the contractually owed service and full payment.
        Ongoing services may be terminated by either party in text form with 30 days' notice to
        the end of the month, unless otherwise agreed in the individual contract.
      </p>
      <p>
        The right to extraordinary termination for good cause remains unaffected for both parties.
        In the event of premature termination of a project contract by the Client without good
        cause, the Contractor's claim to remuneration for the work performed up to that point
        remains in place.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 11 Force majeure</h2>
      <p>
        Neither party is liable for non-performance of its contractual obligations if such
        non-performance is due to circumstances beyond its control (force majeure). This includes,
        in particular, natural disasters, pandemics, official orders, strikes and large-scale
        cyberattacks or failures of external infrastructure. The affected party must inform the
        other party without undue delay.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 12 Final provisions</h2>
      <p>The law of the Federal Republic of Germany applies, excluding the UN Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods.</p>
      <p>
        If the Client is a merchant, a legal entity under public law or a special fund under public
        law, the exclusive place of jurisdiction for all disputes arising from this contract is
        the Contractor's place of business (Elmshorn, Germany).
      </p>
      <p>
        Should individual provisions of these Terms be or become invalid, the validity of the
        remaining provisions shall remain unaffected. The invalid provision shall be replaced by
        a provision that comes closest to what was economically intended.
      </p>
      <p>
        Amendments or additions to this contract require text form. This also applies to any
        cancellation of this text-form clause itself.
      </p>
    </LegalContent>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
